{{Spanish name|Abon|Lee}} [[File:Alfredo Abon Lee.jpg|thumb|Alfredo Abon Lee in 2008]] Captain '''Alfredo Abón Lee''' (1927 – December 4, 2012)<ref name=oo>{{cite web | url=http://www.legacy.com/obituaries/northjersey/obituary.aspx?pid=161514826 | title=View Alfredo Abon's Obituary on NorthJersey.com and share memories}}</ref> was a [[Cuba]]n army officer of [[Chinese Cubans|Chinese Cuban]] ancestry who was the commander of the garrison at [[Yaguajay, Cuba|Yaguajay]] Squadron and was sent to Las Villa, replacing Colonel Roger Rojas Lavernia,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://cubamason.forosactivos.net/t5923-fallece-en-el-destierro-alfredo-abon-lee|title=Fallece en el destierro Alfredo Abon Lee|publisher=}}</ref> where he fought the [[26th of July Movement]] in December 1958 in [[Battle of Yaguajay|one of the final engagements]] of the [[Cuban Revolution]].<ref>[http://www.hero.cult.cu/monumento/yaguajaymultimedia.php Capítulo V – La Batalla de Yaguajay] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20081006215916/http://www.hero.cult.cu/monumento/yaguajaymultimedia.php |date=2008-10-06 }}, Museo Monumento Nacional Camilo Cienfuegos</ref><ref>[http://www.radiocaribe.co.cu/secundaria/historia/103.htm La Batalla de Yaguajay] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100104204350/http://www.radiocaribe.co.cu/Secundaria/Historia/103.htm |date=2010-01-04 }}, Radio Caribe en la Isla de la Juventud Cuba</ref> Before that, he served in the Battalion 22 during operations in eastern Cuba.
He died on December 4, 2012 in [[Englewood, New Jersey]], [[United States]].<ref name=oo/>
