[[File:The Tadas Ivanauskas Zoological Museum.jpg|thumb|Inside the Tadas Ivanauskas Zoological Museum]]

The '''Tadas Ivanauskas Zoological Museum''' was established in [[Kaunas]], [[Lithuania]], in 1919 by [[Tadas Ivanauskas]] (1882–1970).

The museum collects and exhibits various animals: hunting trophies, [[Taxidermy|stuffed animals]], [[Insect collecting|insect collections]], skeletons, dissections.<ref name=official/> It is also an educational and research institution that has four branches: [[bird ringing]] stations in [[Ventė Cape]] and [[Juodkrantė]], nature reserves in [[Čepkeliai Marsh]] and [[Lake Žuvintas]].<ref name=official/>

